<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id372115f5-2930-11f1-b70e-e9fd6f164ed0" identifier="/us/usc/t3/s456"><num value="456">§ 456.</num><heading> Confidentiality</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id372115f6-2930-11f1-b70e-e9fd6f164ed0" identifier="/us/usc/t3/s456/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Counseling</inline>.—</heading><content>All counseling under section 452 shall be strictly confidential, except that, with the consent of the covered employee, the employing office may be notified.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id372115f7-2930-11f1-b70e-e9fd6f164ed0" identifier="/us/usc/t3/s456/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Mediation</inline>.—</heading><content>All mediation under section 452 shall be strictly confidential.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id372115f8-2930-11f1-b70e-e9fd6f164ed0">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/104/331/s2/a">Pub. L. 104–331, § 2(a)</ref>, <date date="1996-10-26">Oct. 26, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/4068">110 Stat. 4068</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
